
'''Al Beroni''' or '''Al Beruni University'''  ({{lang-fa|دانشگاه البیرونی}},  {{Lang-ps|البیرونی پوهنتون}}) is a [[public university]] in [[Afghanistan]]. It was established in 1998 by [[Ahmad Shah Massoud]]. The university is named after [[Abu Rayhan Biruni|Abū Rayḥān Muḥammad ibn Aḥmad Bīrūnī]] ({{lang-fa|ابوریحان محمد بن احمد بیرونی}}), a renowned [[polymath]] scholar who lived in 11th century [[Greater Khorasan|Khorasan]].

Al Beruni University is located next to Gulbahar Textile Company in the [[Kohistan District, Kapisa| Kohistan district]] of [[Kapisa Province]], 70 miles north of [[Kabul]]. Over 1,500 students are enrolled in the university.  The current chancellor is Rashid Khan Aziz Kohistani.  The university has seven departments:
* [[Agriculture]]
* [[Engineering]]
* [[Law]] and [[political science]]
* [[Literature]] and [[journalism]]
* [[Medicine|Medical science]]
* Theology ([[Sharia|Sharayiat]]) 

